<paragraph id="1F76702EFFA7F24E4D65FC459298FB1C" blockId="7.[801,1452,929,1818]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
JEANMONOD &amp; GAMISANS 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A4EFC4593DFFC5F" box="[1132,1255,994,1018]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
(Fl. 
<collectingCountry id="67DE30BEFFA7F24E4AB9FC4593DFFC5F" box="[1179,1255,994,1017]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Corsica</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, ed. 2: 225, 2013) mentionnent ce taxon sous 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4A6BFBA59452FB9C" authority="Berher" authorityName="Berher" authorityYear="1887" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="temulentum" subSpecies="linicola">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A6BFBA5922BFBBC" box="[1097,1299,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Lolium temulentum</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4B43FBA59293FBBC" box="[1377,1451,1026,1050]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">linicola</emphasis>
Berher
</taxonomicName>
en indiquant: 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A27FB859329FB9C" bold="true" box="[1029,1041,1058,1082]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">«</emphasis>
me sm – Cultures de ceréales et de lin; Siscu, Bastelica, non revu depuis 1878 – D?», mention issue de BRIQUET (
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4DB1FBC5930CFBDF" box="[915,1076,1122,1146]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
Prodr. Fl. 
<collectingCountry id="67DE30BEFFA7F24E4DDFFBC5930CFBDF" box="[1021,1076,1122,1145]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Corse</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
1: 178, 1910) qui indique «Marine de Sisco (Gillot in 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4DC4FB2593AAFB3F" box="[998,1170,1154,1178]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Bull. Soc. Bot. Fr.</emphasis>
XXIV, 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4AC2FB25927EFB3F" box="[1248,1350,1154,1177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Sess. Extr.</emphasis>
XLVIII); Bastelica (Reverchon exsicc. cit.)» [ann. 1878, sub. 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4B19FB0592BCFB1C" box="[1339,1412,1186,1210]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linicola">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4B19FB0592BCFB1C" box="[1339,1412,1186,1210]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">linicola</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
!].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1F76702EFFA7F24E4D65FB65921FF95F" blockId="7.[801,1452,929,1818]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">
Nous avons réexaminé les échantillons de Bastelica «Bastelica, moissons, 22.6.187 8, 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A19FB4593CCFB5F" box="[1083,1268,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Reverchon, E. s.n.</emphasis>
(G, G-BU)» qui s’avèrent tous être en fait 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4A6AFAA69201FABF" box="[1096,1337,1281,1305]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Micropyrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tenellum">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A6AFAA69201FABF" bold="true" box="[1096,1337,1281,1305]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Micropyrum tenellum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) Link (= 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4D1DFA859341FA9C" authority="(Viv.) Rchb." authorityName="Rchb." baseAuthorityName="Viv." box="[831,1145,1314,1338]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Nardurus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="halleri">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4D1DFA8594D0FA9C" box="[831,1000,1314,1338]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Nardurus halleri</emphasis>
(Viv.) Rchb.
</taxonomicName>
). Les deux taxons sont morphologiquement proches et peuvent facilement être confondus si on n’examine pas avec attention la structure de l’épillet et le nombre de glumes (2 chez 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4A61FA2593F9FA3F" box="[1091,1217,1410,1433]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Micropyrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4A61FA2593F9FA3F" box="[1091,1217,1410,1433]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Micropyrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
et 1 chez 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4B0DFA259241FA3C" box="[1327,1401,1410,1434]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4B0DFA259241FA3C" box="[1327,1401,1410,1434]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Lolium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). La deuxième mention vient du compte rendu de l’excursion de la Société botanique de 
<collectingCountry id="67DE30BEFFA7F24E4A08FA65934CFA7F" box="[1066,1140,1474,1497]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">France</collectingCountry>
en 
<collectingCountry id="67DE30BEFFA7F24E4ABFFA6593E6FA7C" box="[1181,1246,1474,1498]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Corse</collectingCountry>
en 1877 où Gillot écrit: «Quelques-uns ont poussé jusqu’à Sisco […] en rapportant entre autres plantes intéressantes […] 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4B30F9A59461F99C" authority="Sond" authorityName="Sond" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="linicola">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4B30F9A59294F9BC" box="[1298,1452,1538,1562]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Lolium linicola</emphasis>
Sond
</taxonomicName>
». Cette mention est invérifiable car on ne sait si la plante a été séchée en herbier, par quel collecteur et dans quel herbier elle pourrait être éventuellement déposée. Il est très probable qu’il s’agisse du 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4DEBF925937EF93F" box="[969,1094,1666,1689]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Micropyrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4DEBF925937EF93F" box="[969,1094,1666,1689]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Micropyrum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, taxon commun fleurissant à cette époque et non cité par ailleurs dans le texte. De ce fait, nous considérons que 
<taxonomicName id="D8C90BADFFA7F24E4DF1F9659345F97F" box="[979,1149,1730,1754]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lolium" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="7" pageNumber="82" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotum">
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4DF1F9659345F97F" box="[979,1149,1730,1754]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Lolium remotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
n’a probablement jamais été présent en 
<collectingCountry id="67DE30BEFFA7F24E4DB4F94594EDF95C" box="[918,981,1762,1786]" name="France" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">Corse</collectingCountry>
et 
<emphasis id="2DBDAC3CFFA7F24E4DD4F946921FF95F" bold="true" box="[1014,1319,1761,1786]" pageId="7" pageNumber="82">qu’il faut le rayer de la flore.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
